<paragraph blockId="1.[174,1233,1772,1851]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
1. Orbit with opalescent or matt, microtrichose area at level of antenna base (
<figureCitation box="[970,1020,1772,1794]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[173,206,1383,1405]" captionTargetBox="[207,1168,189,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-116@11.[205,1179,174,1361]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Afropyrgota uzungwa sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior); 4 — mesonotum dorsal; 5 — wing; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior and abdomen, ventrolateral. Scale bar 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404204/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">fig. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1030,1041,1772,1794]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,604,626]" captionTargetBox="[202,1177,169,589]" captionTargetId="figure-456@4.[195,1196,158,590]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Afropyrgota copelandi sp. n., ♀: 1 — sternite 6 and oviscape, ventrolateral view; 2 — same, lateroventral and dorsomedial lobes, left; 3 — aculeus; 4 — vagina and ventral receptacle; 5 — spermatheca. dl — dorsal lobe; lvl — lateroventral lobe; mva — medioventral desclerotized area; st6 — sternite 6; vr — ventral receptacle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404031/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis box="[1030,1041,1772,1794]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Wing yellow with slightly darker apex (
<figureCitation box="[449,493,1801,1823]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[173,206,1383,1405]" captionTargetBox="[207,1168,189,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-116@11.[205,1179,174,1361]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Afropyrgota uzungwa sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior); 4 — mesonotum dorsal; 5 — wing; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior and abdomen, ventrolateral. Scale bar 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404204/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">fig 7</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis box="[502,536,1801,1823]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<figureCitation box="[502,514,1801,1823]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1690,1712]" captionTargetBox="[206,1214,593,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-190@3.[189,1218,578,1671]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Afropyrgota copelandi sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior view); 4 — wing; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior; 9, 10 — abdomen (9 — dorsal, 10 — lateral view). fo — femoral organ." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404029/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[525,536,1801,1823]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[173,206,1732,1754]" captionTargetBox="[232,1182,721,1694]" captionTargetId="figure-268@7.[225,1182,709,1696]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5. Afropyrgota marshalli, holotype Ơ: 1 — lateral view; 2 — labels, 3 — wing; 4 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 5 — epandrium, right view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404039/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">5</figureCitation>
</emphasis>
). Thorax, femora and abdomen dark reddish brown, black setulose. Scutellum with 3 pairs of sctl (
<figureCitation box="[504,554,1829,1851]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[173,206,1383,1405]" captionTargetBox="[207,1168,189,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-116@11.[205,1179,174,1361]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Afropyrgota uzungwa sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior); 4 — mesonotum dorsal; 5 — wing; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior and abdomen, ventrolateral. Scale bar 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404204/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">fig. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[563,574,1829,1851]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[170,203,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[196,1183,399,1656]" captionTargetId="figure-78@6.[195,1196,394,1665]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Afropyrgota marshalli, ♀: 1 — lateral view; 2–4 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — wing; 7 — mid femur, anterior view; 8 — oviscape, ventrolateral; 9 — same, lateroventral lobe; 10 — aculeus; 11 — spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404035/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis box="[563,574,1829,1851]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">4</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). WL&gt; 
<quantity box="[654,725,1829,1851]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[733,825,1829,1851]" name="Tanzania" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. ....................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[970,1175,1829,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Afropyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uzungwa" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[970,1175,1829,1851]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Afropyrgota uzungwa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1181,1233,1829,1851]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,571]" box="[166,1225,175,197]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead box="[166,1225,175,197]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
— Orbit entirely shining. WL &lt;
<quantity box="[522,593,175,197]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
. Other characters variable. ............................................................... 2.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
2. Mesonotum densely and long black setulose (
<figureCitation box="[689,741,204,226]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[209,1194,805,1654]" captionTargetId="figure-224@5.[205,1202,802,1660]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig.3. Afropyrgota mambilla sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2– 4 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — oviscape, lateroventral; 9 — same, apex, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404033" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404033/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[752,763,204,226]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,604,626]" captionTargetBox="[202,1177,169,589]" captionTargetId="figure-456@4.[195,1196,158,590]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Afropyrgota copelandi sp. n., ♀: 1 — sternite 6 and oviscape, ventrolateral view; 2 — same, lateroventral and dorsomedial lobes, left; 3 — aculeus; 4 — vagina and ventral receptacle; 5 — spermatheca. dl — dorsal lobe; lvl — lateroventral lobe; mva — medioventral desclerotized area; st6 — sternite 6; vr — ventral receptacle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404031" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404031/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[752,763,204,226]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with 3 pairs of sctl (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1137,204,226]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[209,1194,805,1654]" captionTargetId="figure-224@5.[205,1202,802,1660]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig.3. Afropyrgota mambilla sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2– 4 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — oviscape, lateroventral; 9 — same, apex, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404033" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404033/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1149,1160,204,226]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[173,206,1732,1754]" captionTargetBox="[232,1182,721,1694]" captionTargetId="figure-268@7.[225,1182,709,1696]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5. Afropyrgota marshalli, holotype Ơ: 1 — lateral view; 2 — labels, 3 — wing; 4 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 5 — epandrium, right view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404039/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[1149,1160,204,226]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Proepisternal ridge with 8–10 long setae. Oviscape with 2 yellow hook-like, anteromesally directed lobes (
<figureCitation box="[248,298,261,283]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[209,1194,805,1654]" captionTargetId="figure-224@5.[205,1202,802,1660]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig.3. Afropyrgota mambilla sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2– 4 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — oviscape, lateroventral; 9 — same, apex, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404033" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404033/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[307,318,261,283]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,1732,1754]" captionTargetBox="[335,1069,1238,1711]" captionTargetId="figure-108@12.[309,1083,1230,1712]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 9. Afropyrgota, ♀ abdominal sternites, macerated, ventral view: 1 — A. copelandi sp. n.; 2 — A. marshalli; 3 — A. uzungwa sp. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404208/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[307,318,261,283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">9</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Wing grey microtrichose with two darker marks. Female mid femur yellowish setulose, without femoral organ (
<figureCitation box="[428,478,290,312]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[209,1194,805,1654]" captionTargetId="figure-224@5.[205,1202,802,1660]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig.3. Afropyrgota mambilla sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2– 4 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — oviscape, lateroventral; 9 — same, apex, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404033" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404033/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[487,498,290,312]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[173,206,1383,1405]" captionTargetBox="[207,1168,189,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-116@11.[205,1179,174,1361]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Afropyrgota uzungwa sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior); 4 — mesonotum dorsal; 5 — wing; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior and abdomen, ventrolateral. Scale bar 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404204/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[487,498,290,312]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">7</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[518,592,290,312]" name="Nigeria" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
. ............................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[957,1168,290,312]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Afropyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mambilla" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[957,1168,290,312]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Afropyrgota mambilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1174,1225,290,312]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="27">— Mesonotum moderately short reddish brown setulose. Scutellum with 1–2 pairs of sctl. Proepisternal ridge with 2–6 moderately short setae. Oviscape without such lobes. Wing and mid femur variable. ..... 3.</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
3. Scutellum with one pair of sctl (
<figureCitation box="[560,610,377,399]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1690,1712]" captionTargetBox="[206,1214,593,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-190@3.[189,1218,578,1671]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Afropyrgota copelandi sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior view); 4 — wing; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior; 9, 10 — abdomen (9 — dorsal, 10 — lateral view). fo — femoral organ." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404029/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[624,635,377,399]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[173,206,1732,1754]" captionTargetBox="[232,1182,721,1694]" captionTargetId="figure-268@7.[225,1182,709,1696]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5. Afropyrgota marshalli, holotype Ơ: 1 — lateral view; 2 — labels, 3 — wing; 4 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 5 — epandrium, right view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404039/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[624,635,377,399]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Frons widely black. Mid femur with very large cuneiform femoral organ almost entirely covering its apical half (
<figureCitation box="[760,807,405,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1690,1712]" captionTargetBox="[206,1214,593,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-190@3.[189,1218,578,1671]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Afropyrgota copelandi sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior view); 4 — wing; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior; 9, 10 — abdomen (9 — dorsal, 10 — lateral view). fo — femoral organ." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404029" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404029/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[819,830,405,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[173,206,1383,1405]" captionTargetBox="[207,1168,189,1353]" captionTargetId="figure-116@11.[205,1179,174,1361]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Afropyrgota uzungwa sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2, 3 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior); 4 — mesonotum dorsal; 5 — wing; 6 — fore leg, posterior; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior and abdomen, ventrolateral. Scale bar 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404204/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[819,830,405,427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">7</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[849,913,405,427]" name="Kenya" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Kenya</collectingCountry>
. ..... 
<taxonomicName authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[958,1168,405,427]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Afropyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="copelandi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[958,1168,405,427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Afropyrgota copelandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1174,1225,405,427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,571]" box="[166,1225,434,456]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead box="[166,1225,434,456]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">— Scutellum with two pairs of sctl. Frons and mid femur variable. ............................................................... 4.</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
4. Body entirely reddish yellow setulose, including pleura, abdomen and legs. Mid femur with cuneiform femoral organ narrower than femur (
<figureCitation box="[598,668,492,514]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1710,1732]" captionTargetBox="[206,1193,536,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-147@9.[206,1194,536,1678]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig.6. Afropyrgota ota sp. n., ♀: 1 — holotype, lateral view; 2–4 — head (2 —left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 5 — wing; 6 — mid leg, anterior; 7 — prosternum, anteroventral; 8 — paratype abdomen, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404041" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404041/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
fig. 6, 
<emphasis box="[657,668,492,514]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">6</emphasis>
